contents.name: Community Counselling
contents.description: Counselling Services provided by trained professionals. Suitable for people with mental health conditions such as anxiety, depression, or eating disorders as well as people experiencing difficult life events and circumstances.
contents.interpretation_services: Interpretation services are available in Urdu, Polish, and Slovak
contents.application_process: If you are an NHS patient please ask your GP for a referral letter, we will then be in touch with you directly. If you are not an NHS patient you should ring our reception to arrange an appointment
contents.fees_description: Non-NHS patients are expected to pay for their counselling sessions. We charge a flat rate per hour of counselling. The current rate is £50 per hour. Please see our website for up to date prices.
contents.accreditations: All of our practitioners are accredited by the BASC, UKCP, and the Professional Standards Body
contents.eligibility_description: This service is intended for all people aged 12 and over who require counselling services in the MyCity area
contents.alert: Following COVID-19 we have moved most of our counselling sessions online. Please contact the reception if you require further information.

program.name: Community Mental Health Support
program.description: Comprehensive Mental Health Services available to residents of MyCity including CBT and Counselling. This is not an emergency service and should not be used as an alternative to hospital and GP services.
